<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>cover the ground • cover the territory</xh5><p> <i>cover the ground—</i>1. <i>(also: cover ground)</i> deal with an assignment, etc. (especially efficiently or rapidly): His supporters just couldn’t <u>cover the ground</u> fast enough to capitalize on the sudden shift in public sentiment. 2. <i>(of a book, etc.)</i> treat a subject: The author’s statements, as to testing the cement before it was accepted, are very instructive and seem to <u>cover the ground</u> most thoroughly.</p><p> <i>cover the territory</i>—(also: cover the field) be comprehensive: The book really <u>covers the territory</u> in terms of outlining the medical treatment options, their pluses and minuses.</p> </entry>
